ew&	ext{Ethndananc$$ (9.50) 7. *Ozonolysis* : Ozonolysis of alkenes involves the addition of ozone molecule to alkene to form ozonide, and then cleavage of the ozonide by Zn-H2O to smaller molecules. This reaction is highly useful in detecting the position of the double bond in alkenes or other unsaturated compounds. $$ egin{aligned} 	ext{CH}\_3	ext{CH=CH}\_2 + 	ext{O}\_3 &\longrightarrow 	ext{CH}\_3	ext{-CH}\_2 \ 	ext{Propene} &\qquad 	ext{Propene ozonide} \ &\qquad 	ext{Propene ozonide} \ &\qquad \downarrow 	ext{Zn} + 	ext{H}\_2	ext{O} \ &\qquad 	ext{CH}\_3	ext{-CHO} \ &\qquad 	ext{Ethanol} \ 	ext{H}\_3	ext{C} &\qquad 	ext{H}\_3	ext{C} 	imes 	ext{O}\_3 \ &\qquad 	ext{H}\_3	ext{C} 	imes 	ext{O}\_3 \ &\qquad 	ext{H}\_3	ext{C} 	imes 	ext{H}\_2	ext{O} \ &\qquad 	ext{H}\_3	ext{C} 	imes 	ext{H}\_2	ext{O} \ &\qquad 	ext{2-Methylpropene} \ &\qquad 	ext{H}\_3	ext{C} 	imes 	ext{H}\_2	ext{O} \ &\qquad 	ext{H}\_3	ext{C} 	imes 	ext{O} + 	ext{HCHO} \ &\qquad 	ext{Prrapan-2-one} \end{aligned} 	ag{9.55}$$ 8. *Polymerisation:* You are familiar with polythene bags and polythene sheets. Polythene is obtained by the combination of large number of ethene molecules at high temperature, high pressure and in the presence of a catalyst. The large molecules thus obtained are called polymers. This reaction is known as polymerisation. The simple compounds from which polymers are made are called Unit 9.indd 313 03-05-2024 16:08:51 monomers. Other alkenes also undergo polymerisation. ![](_page_19_Figure_2.jpeg) Polymers are used for the manufacture of plastic bags, squeeze bottles, refrigerator dishes, toys, pipes, radio and T.V. cabinets etc. Polypropene is used for the manufacture of milk crates, plastic buckets and other moulded articles. Though these materials have now become common, excessive use of polythene and polypropylene is a matter of great concern for all of us. ####
